WEBVTT

p01
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.154
Open the IT and Support module and look at the left rail.

p02
00:00:04.154 --> 00:00:05.724
Two groups organize it.

p03
00:00:05.724 --> 00:00:11.493
Support sits at the top, holding the tickets, the help desk, and the alerts you work every day.

p04
00:00:11.493 --> 00:00:13.638
Audit sits underneath, for the history questions.

p05
00:00:13.638 --> 00:00:16.968
Today, two of those Support entries are the whole job.

p06
00:00:16.968 --> 00:00:17.887
Let's find them.

p07
00:00:18.346 --> 00:00:19.544
First, the Knowledge Base.

p08
00:00:19.544 --> 00:00:23.849
It's in the Support group, tucked between the help desk and the alerts.

p09
00:00:23.849 --> 00:00:26.082
Picture it as the team's memory.

p10
00:00:26.082 --> 00:00:32.405
A tech works out a fix, writes it down once, and from then on the answer is a search away.

p11
00:00:32.405 --> 00:00:36.000
Nobody has to solve the same problem from scratch a second time.

p12
00:00:36.457 --> 00:00:36.993
Open it.

p13
00:00:37.963 --> 00:00:39.732
Here's the honest part of this lesson.

p14
00:00:40.088 --> 00:00:43.083
On the day we verified, the page did not load.

p15
00:00:43.398 --> 00:00:47.271
It came back with a plain not-found error, a four oh four, and nothing else on the screen.

p16
00:00:47.472 --> 00:00:48.875
So the article list, the way it's organized, the write-ups themselves,

p17
00:00:49.299 --> 00:00:54.952
none of that can be shown to you yet.

p18
00:00:55.394 --> 00:00:57.087
This is the reflex worth building.

p19
00:00:57.316 --> 00:01:01.011
A page is missing, you record exactly that, and you flag it.

p20
00:01:01.380 --> 00:01:03.397
You never paint in the blank from memory.

p21
00:01:04.024 --> 00:01:06.528
Once it does render, here's why it earns your time.

p22
00:01:07.038 --> 00:01:10.344
The Knowledge Base is where the how-to and troubleshooting write-ups live.

p23
00:01:10.833 --> 00:01:12.070
The team norm is simple: close a ticket that taught you something reusable,

p24
00:01:12.356 --> 00:01:16.715
and you document it here before you move on.

p25
00:01:17.154 --> 00:01:21.798
The next tech inherits the answer in seconds instead of retracing your whole afternoon.

p26
00:01:22.371 --> 00:01:24.020
Back to the rail.

p27
00:01:24.020 --> 00:01:26.270
Find Training Requests, just under System Alerts.

p28
00:01:26.270 --> 00:01:28.424
This is the client-training pipeline.

p29
00:01:28.424 --> 00:01:33.569
Your team files into it and works out of it, so it runs in both directions.

p30
00:01:34.160 --> 00:01:34.610
Open it.

p31
00:01:35.339 --> 00:01:36.784
Same story as before.

p32
00:01:37.405 --> 00:01:41.906
On verification day it returned the same not-found error and did not render.

p33
00:01:42.227 --> 00:01:44.992
The counts, the request types, the columns, all parked until a live pass can confirm them.

p34
00:01:45.327 --> 00:01:47.967
So you do the same thing you did a moment ago.

p35
00:01:48.265 --> 00:01:50.352
Record the missing page.

p36
00:01:50.636 --> 00:01:56.607
Resist the urge to rebuild it from an old screenshot in your head.

p37
00:01:56.607 --> 00:01:59.995
What it's for, so you're ready when it comes back.

p38
00:01:59.995 --> 00:02:02.851
Training Requests follows a client's ask from the first request,

p39
00:02:02.851 --> 00:02:05.136
through scheduling, to a session that's actually done.

p40
00:02:05.136 --> 00:02:06.564
You'll use it two ways.

p41
00:02:06.564 --> 00:02:09.626
You file a request when a site asks for training,

p42
00:02:09.626 --> 00:02:13.203
and you pick requests up when it's your turn to deliver.

p43
00:02:13.203 --> 00:02:14.484
Now glance back at the header.

p44
00:02:14.987 --> 00:02:18.701
Search and Ask Shyne stay pinned up here on every page.

p45
00:02:19.038 --> 00:02:21.981
That matters most on a day exactly like this one.

p46
00:02:22.401 --> 00:02:26.835
When a page won't open, control K still jumps you anywhere in the platform,

p47
00:02:27.121 --> 00:02:30.278
and Shyne can answer a plain question while the page is down.

p48
00:02:30.737 --> 00:02:36.278
One rule holds: confirm whatever Shyne tells you before you act on it.

p49
00:02:36.278 --> 00:02:37.258
So, the recap.

p50
00:02:37.908 --> 00:02:43.945
Knowledge Base and Training Requests both live right here, under Support, inside IT and Support.

p51
00:02:44.741 --> 00:02:49.062
Today both came back empty, a four oh four, so their contents stay parked.

p52
00:02:49.776 --> 00:02:51.920
The lesson was never the page you couldn't see.

p53
00:02:52.306 --> 00:02:53.749
It's the habit underneath it.

p54
00:02:54.456 --> 00:02:56.768
Find the destination, read its real state, and when it's missing, report it instead of guessing.

p55
00:02:57.100 --> 00:03:03.255
That reflex is what keeps this training honest.

